combtxt:WHILE PULLING ACROSS JACINTO PORT BLVD PORT JOB 384 COLLIDED WITH A TRUCK THAT FAILED TO STOP AT THE  CROSSING. EYE WITNESSES STATE THAT THE TRUCK APPEARED TO NOT SEE THE TRAIN AS HE DID NOT APPLY HIS BRAKES. THEY ALSO SAID THE TRAIN WAS CLEARLY BLOWING THE HORN AND SOUNDING THE WHISTLE PRIOR TO THE CROSSING AND SUBSEQUENT IMPACT. :inci
